column9: Formulary Status Definitions for Managed Care Grid
Preferred: Strips are covered on Tier 1 or Tier 2 at the lowest co-pay

Non Formulary: Strips are available on Tier 3 at an equal or greater co-pay OR not reimbursed (i.e.the plan does not pay for this drug or the individual will need to pay for it if desired). [Note, this combines the formerly known as covered and not covered].
DME: Strips are covered only through Durable Medical Equipment.
Open Access: All equally covered/same co-pay (Rx Benefit)

eVoucher: active in 16 states & 2 MSA's (AZ, CT, IA, ID, IL, IN, KS, MN, NE, NM, OK, OR, PA, TX, WA, WI, Tallahassee FL, NY Metro), ONLY works if no step edits, blocks, etc. Use this instead of "Non Formulary" if the plan is active where eVoucher is turned on and if there is only a co-pay differential for OT (no edits or blocks in place against OT).
